      {
        "parameters": {
          "promptType": "define",
          "text": "={{ $json.historyText }}",
          "options": {
            "systemMessage": "You turn a chat conversation into a single atomic note (Zettelkasten style). Read the conversation and produce ONE JSON object with exactly these keys: {\"title\": a short title, \"text\": the note body as clear prose, \"tags\": an array of 3-6 short lowercase topical tags relevant to the content}. Output ONLY the JSON object. Do not save anything, do not call tools, do not add any text outside the JSON.",
            "enableStreaming": false
          }
        },
        "id": "6a5ef2c3-0b6a-4526-8edc-80d41fbfb431",
        "name": "Draft Agent",
        "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
        "typeVersion": 3.1,
        "position": [
          680,
          180
        ]
      },
      {
        "parameters": {
          "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
          "options": {
            "temperature": 0.3
          }
        },
        "id": "f5b00300-f612-4497-b254-d67212f1d3a2",
        "name": "Draft Model",
        "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatGroq",
        "typeVersion": 1,
        "position": [
          680,
          360
        ],
        "credentials": {
          "groqApi": {
            "id": "woCh9CG7qUGXmSCX",
            "name": "Groq account"
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "parameters": {
          "jsCode": "let raw = ($input.first().json.output || '').toString();\nraw = raw.replace(/<think>[\\s\\S]*?<\\/think>/gi,'').replace(/<\\|think\\|>[\\s\\S]*?<\\|\\/?think\\|>/gi,'').replace(/<\\|?\\/?think\\|?>/gi,'').replace(/```(?:json)?/gi,'').trim();\nlet o = {};\ntry { const m = raw.match(/\\{[\\s\\S]*\\}/); if (m) o = JSON.parse(m[0]); } catch(e) {}\nconst title = (o.title || '').toString().slice(0,500);\nconst text = (o.text || '').toString();\nlet tags = Array.isArray(o.tags) ? o.tags : (typeof o.tags === 'string' ? o.tags.split(',') : []);\ntags = tags.map(t => t.toString().trim().toLowerCase()).filter(Boolean).slice(0,8);\nconst draft_id = 'd_' + Date.now() + '_' + Math.random().toString(36).slice(2,8);\nreturn [{ json: { draft_id, question: null, title, text, tags } }];"
        },
        "id": "41969cc2-65b2-40a1-a5de-bd6e2850eaac",
        "name": "Parse Draft",
        "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
        "typeVersion": 2,
        "position": [
          900,
          180
        ]
      },
      {
        "parameters": {
          "promptType": "define",
          "text": "={{ $json.feedback }}",
          "options": {
            "systemMessage": "=You are refining a draft note based on the user's feedback. Work from the CURRENT DRAFT and the refinement conversation below.\n\nCURRENT DRAFT:\n{{ $json.draftText }}\n\nREFINEMENT CONVERSATION SO FAR:\n{{ $json.refineText }}\n\nApply the user's latest feedback (the Human message) and return ONE JSON object with the UPDATED note: {\"title\":..., \"text\":..., \"tags\":[3-6 short lowercase tags]}. If \u2014 and ONLY if \u2014 you genuinely cannot proceed without clarification, instead return {\"question\": \"your question\"}. Output ONLY the JSON, nothing else.",
            "enableStreaming": false
          }
        },
        "id": "db8d7199-85a7-43d0-9c55-ee07c8ef7a36",
        "name": "Refine Agent",
        "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
        "typeVersion": 3.1,
        "position": [
          680,
          460
        ]
      },
      {
        "parameters": {
